1
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:41,200
Officer He.

2
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:43,120
Honey. One mutton rice noodle.

3
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:44,400
- Extra coriander.
- Alright.

4
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:46,600
To go. Make it fast.

5
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,400
Officer He. We haven't seen you in ages.

6
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:50,520
The criminal department
is busier than the station?

7
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:52,320
I'll be back in three days.

8
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:55,600
That's good. That's good.
We're all eager to have you back.

9
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:59,560
Officer He.
There's a newcomer at the station.

10
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:00,880
Officer… Officer Qu.

11
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:04,320
We've never seen him smile.
Difficult person.

12
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:07,640
Tell everyone to be at ease.

13
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:10,800
Once I'm back,
I'll get that poker face out of here.

14
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:13,720
Wait. One more noodle. No coriander.

15
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,800
Alright. One more noodle. No coriander.

16
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:17,240
- Alright.
- I'm on it.

17
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,160
POLICE CODE OF CONDUCT
ON UNIFORM AND APPEARANCE

18
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:21,680
I haven't slept for days.

19
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:22,600
CONFERENCE ROOM

20
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:24,040
Seriously.

21
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:27,280
Good to see you, guys.

22
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,400
Have one.

23
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:31,080
I don't smoke. Thanks.

24
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:35,200
Hi.

25
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:38,720
Writing notes?

26
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,040
- Let's eat after this.
- Okay.

27
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:46,960
Get up.

28
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:52,000
Same old rules. Long story short.

29
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:54,200
Last night,

30
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:57,600
there was a major burglary
at the Dongshan Mine.

31
00:03:57,680 --> 00:04:00,800
Valuable items
and important materials were lost.

32
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:03,200
My higher-ups were on my neck all night.

33
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:04,880
From now on,

34
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:09,920
whoever doesn't have important tasks
will join the Special Task Force.

35
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,080
Tan. Give out the materials.

36
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:17,519
- Big cases? Ours?
- You in?

37
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:22,280
Captain.

38
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:26,560
Of course, we should
prioritize the big case.

39
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:28,520
Captain Feng.

40
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:32,360
Fangxu.

41
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:34,600
You already got ideas?

42
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:36,160
Tell us about it.

43
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:40,400
Everyone here will get to hear
the ideas of a PPSUC graduate.

44
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,080
Captain Feng.

45
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:52,080
The missing persons case
I'm working on is also quite urgent.

46
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:56,320
Seriously?

47
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,480
Seriously?

48
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:03,000
Yuanhang.

49
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:06,840
Has the case in Yuanlongli been filed?

50
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:08,520
Not yet.

51
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,920
How long have you been on this?

52
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,120
Four days.

53
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:15,480
They've been investigating
around the clock,

54
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:19,040
as busy as bees, 24 hours non-stop.

55
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:24,640
Yuanhang.

56
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:26,880
It's been four days.

57
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:29,520
We can't file a case
without finding the person.

58
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:32,000
But based on what we know,

59
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:34,680
this case is highly likely
to develop into a murder.

60
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:38,080
What makes you think
it's going to be a murder?

61
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:41,760
Is that based on proof or your intuition?

62
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:46,600
Captain Feng.

63
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:48,720
On probability.

64
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:52,960
Approximately 25% of missing persons cases
are ultimately classified as homicides.

65
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:56,480
For every four missing people,
one dies of unnatural causes.

66
00:05:56,560 --> 00:06:00,480
And now we've passed the golden 72 hours
for finding the missing person.

67
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:03,880
Every extra day means more danger
to the missing person.

68
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,280
That's all.

69
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:23,880
Captain, this kid is a bookworm.

70
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:25,640
Please don't mind him.

71
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:27,400
You think I don't know that?

72
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:30,520
I was also annoyingly stubborn
when I was young.

73
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:34,240
This kid is persistent.

74
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:36,120
He'll make a good officer.

75
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:38,840
But then again,

76
00:06:41,320 --> 00:06:43,800
you are also to blame
for his stubbornness.

77
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:46,360
You've been mentoring him for days.

78
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:47,800
Is this how you train him?

79
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:49,640
How can I mentor a college graduate?

80
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:52,120
Besides, you never said
that I'd be his mentor.

81
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:57,920
Isn't he sure that it's going
to turn into a murder?

82
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:01,520
How about this? Keep an eye on your area.

83
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,920
Transfer Ran Fangxu
to the Special Task Force.

84
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,440
Transfer him here to keep defying you?

85
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:09,360
Also, we're not allowed
to work cases alone.

86
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:10,480
How about this, Captain?

87
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:13,480
Give us an official order and a deadline.

88
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:15,280
This way, he'll have no complaints. Okay?

89
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,240
To be honest, I believe

90
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:22,520
that a missing person matters more
than some lost items.

91
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:30,640
Fine. How many days do you need?

92
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:31,640
Three days.

93
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:34,360
After three days, I'll bring that kid
to the Special Task Force.

94
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:42,640
Captain.

95
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:52,040
When are you going back
to the police station?

96
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:56,520
Also in three days.

97
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,600
Sneaky fox.

98
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:03,320
I…

99
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:07,360
There's nothing in it for me.

100
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:08,800
I did it all for you.

101
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:13,200
Thank you, Officer He.

102
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:14,960
For what?

103
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:17,880
You should thank Captain Feng.
He values talent.

104
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:21,320
Also, stop addressing me so formally.

105
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:24,040
What should I call you?

106
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:28,080
Our partnership will end soon.

107
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:30,920
I won't take advantage of you
and make you call me "sir".

108
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,320
Just call me He.

109
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:39,799
He.

110
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:42,440
I will do my best
to avoid delaying your return.

111
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:50,200
To be honest,
I have some selfish intentions.

112
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:52,720
This case has almost become a joke.

113
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:54,280
I can't go back empty-handed.

114
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:58,160
That's enough. Dig in. Dig in.

115
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,720
Clean it up afterward.

116
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:14,000
You like coriander too?

117
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:16,000
Have this. I'll have this.

118
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:26,160
It's a bit too much.

119
00:09:46,680 --> 00:09:50,000
The case of Dongshan Mine
is the real deal.

120
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:52,680
But you're only interested
in a minor case.

121
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:05,080
My parents also went missing.

122
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:08,720
At first, they said it was nothing.

123
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:12,440
But later, they found…

124
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,520
their bodies.

125
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:49,760
We have three days. We have time.

126
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:57,280
Okay.

127
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,320
Wait.

128
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:16,040
MUSE FOOT MASSAGE, OWNER: ZHAO HONGMEI

129
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,520
MUSE FOOT MASSAGE, OWNER: ZHAO HONGMEI

130
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:21,720
How did I forget about her?

131
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:26,920
MUSE FOOT MASSAGE

132
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:34,080
So annoying.

133
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:45,200
Don't slam the door.

134
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:54,320
We have zero customers
after the police visited.

135
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,720
Not even a fly flew in.

136
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:04,760
It's all because of Mengmeng.

137
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:06,880
Listen.

138
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:09,200
No one is allowed
to mention Mengmeng again.

139
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:12,680
Do not gossip about her to anyone.

140
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:14,200
You hear me?

141
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:18,360
You hear me?

142
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:20,760
Yeah.

143
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,720
Lili. Get a perm.

144
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:27,040
Look at your hair.
It's like a pot of plants.

145
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:28,560
Ms. Zhao.

146
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,680
I need money for that.

147
00:12:30,760 --> 00:12:32,160
You haven't paid me this month.

148
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:42,600
Why are you staring at me?
Do I have money on my face?

149
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:46,160
Still staring? Go get a perm.

150
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:54,320
QINGSONG CEMENT CONNECTS YOU AND ME

151
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:59,800
MUSE FOOT MASSAGE

152
00:13:21,160 --> 00:13:22,480
I don't know Mengmeng so well.

153
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:24,560
I don't know what exactly happened to her.

154
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:25,880
What happened?

155
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:33,320
If I remember correctly,
you wanted to say something that night.

156
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:34,880
No one picked her.

157
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:37,000
She didn't earn anything,
so she stopped coming.

158
00:13:37,640 --> 00:13:38,480
Why did she miss work?

159
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,120
I don't know.

160
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:46,480
Officer, stop pushing me.

161
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:48,400
I… I really don't know.

162
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:50,840
I have things to do. Can I leave now?

163
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:51,760
No.

164
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,040
Did Zhao Hongmei threaten you?

165
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:57,520
I can arrest her
if she's hiding something.

166
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:05,920
Rest assured. The information
you provide will be kept confidential.

167
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,400
- We're just trying to find Mengmeng.
- Yeah.

168
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:20,520
Actually, Mengmeng had some bad luck
right before she disappeared.

169
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:21,640
Bad luck?

170
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:28,560
Speaking of which,
she took the hit for me.

171
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:38,880
MUSE FOOT MASSAGE

172
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:40,120
Mr. Song.

173
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:42,040
Mr. Song.

174
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,600
You finally came to inspect our work.

175
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:46,120
Be careful.

176
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:50,960
Our young ladies have missed you so much.

177
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,160
Wait.

178
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:54,960
Briefcase.

179
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:56,680
Hurry.

180
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:04,280
MUSE FOOT MASSAGE

181
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:10,480
Welcome, Mr. Song.

182
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:12,160
- Mei.
- Yes?

183
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:14,480
I've traveled everywhere.

184
00:15:14,560 --> 00:15:16,360
This is the best place for me.

185
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:19,320
Wherever you say is nice,
that's the nicest place.

186
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:24,400
Don't just stand there.
Hurry up and get around.

187
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:26,840
Get closer to Mr. Song.

188
00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:31,400
Go ahead. Go ahead.

189
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:42,120
Mr. Song. Lili. Get him in.

190
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:46,080
How dare you snatch my things?

191
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:51,200
I'll break your other leg, too.

192
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:02,040
Who are you?

193
00:16:02,120 --> 00:16:04,000
Mr. Song, I'm Lili.

194
00:16:04,920 --> 00:16:06,080
QINGSONG CEMENT

195
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:09,280
Who said you could touch my briefcase?

196
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:11,200
The essential oil might drip on it.

197
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:12,760
Who said you could touch my briefcase?

198
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:13,800
I paid for that.

199
00:16:13,880 --> 00:16:15,640
Who said you could touch my briefcase?

200
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:18,640
How dare you touch my briefcase?

201
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,080
- How dare you!
- Mr. Song.

202
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:21,520
What are you doing? What are you doing?

203
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:23,240
Go away. Go away.

204
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:25,160
Why are you angry with that dumb girl?

205
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:26,840
Don't be mad. I'll get you someone else.

206
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:28,360
Mengmeng.

207
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:30,240
Mengmeng is very sweet.
She'll make you happy.

208
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:32,520
Mengmeng. Hurry.

209
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:37,480
Come on. Mr. Song, this is Mengmeng.
Serve him well.

210
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:48,640
That briefcase says "Qingsong Cement".

211
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:51,040
- So Mr. Song is…
- Song Qingsong.

212
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:54,360
There is only one Mr. Song in Weiyang.

213
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:57,840
Hundreds of people gathered for a fight
outside the cement factory a few days ago.

214
00:16:57,920 --> 00:17:00,040
It was because of him
and Cripple Du of the steel factory.

215
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:03,640
Those two are known to be enemies.

216
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:07,119
SONG QINGSONG

217
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:10,480
Song Qingsong met Xu Meng.
What happened next?

218
00:17:11,119 --> 00:17:14,760
I thought Mr. Song could calm down
after he saw Mengmeng.

219
00:17:14,839 --> 00:17:16,480
But Mengmeng started screaming in there.

220
00:17:16,560 --> 00:17:18,680
And Mr. Song hit her even harder.

221
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:21,160
Why?

222
00:17:22,319 --> 00:17:25,359
I think it was still
because of that briefcase.

223
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:27,359
- How dare you!
- Mr. Song, spare me.

224
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:28,840
Mr. Song, spare me.

225
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:30,000
Shut up.

226
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:31,520
- Still won't admit it?
- I am sorry.

227
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:33,520
Spare me.

228
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:36,240
I can make you disappear from Weiyang.

229
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:37,440
You hear me?

230
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,720
I can make you disappear.

231
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:41,760
I'm sorry.

232
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:43,800
I'm sorry. Spare me.

233
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:45,600
- Still crying?
- Spare me.

234
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:47,040
Spare me.

235
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,680
Still crying, huh?

236
00:17:48,760 --> 00:17:50,080
I can make you disappear!

237
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:53,320
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

238
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:54,560
Spare me.

239
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,640
- Still crying?
- Spare me.

240
00:17:56,720 --> 00:17:59,880
Mr. Song kept beating her in that room.

241
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:02,680
Eventually, she went silent.

242
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:06,200
Song Qingsong said he'd made
Xu Meng disappear from Weiyang?

243
00:18:06,280 --> 00:18:07,320
Yeah.

244
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:10,360
He kept repeating those words.

245
00:18:10,440 --> 00:18:12,000
I heard him clearly.

246
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:15,000
Any idea what's in that briefcase?

247
00:18:15,080 --> 00:18:18,600
White papers. A thick stack.

248
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:20,920
It hurt so much when he hit me with those.

249
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:24,040
Papers? Not money?

250
00:18:25,280 --> 00:18:26,200
Not money.

251
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:28,440
Maybe for rich people,

252
00:18:29,280 --> 00:18:31,280
paper is money,

253
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:35,160
and money sometimes is just paper.

254
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,080
They say, "Life is as fragile as paper."

255
00:18:40,840 --> 00:18:42,360
People like us

256
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:45,680
are worth less than some papers.

257
00:18:56,560 --> 00:18:59,320
Did Song Qingsong and Xu Meng
know each other?

258
00:19:00,040 --> 00:19:02,400
Mengmeng and I used to work in Pattia.

259
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:06,640
Mr. Song often came
and asked for Mengmeng.

260
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:09,320
He wanted to keep her as his mistress.

261
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:10,760
But she turned him down.

262
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:14,280
That's why she got beaten
and sent to the hospital.

263
00:19:15,240 --> 00:19:16,720
Didn't your boss do anything about it?

264
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:18,040
She dared not.

265
00:19:18,120 --> 00:19:21,280
Mr. Song rented her the place.
What could she do?

266
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:29,120
The 18th floor of New York Block
is Song Qingsong's property?

267
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:32,720
He also owns the dorms downstairs.

268
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:35,200
Did Xu Meng tell you
why she turned him down?

269
00:19:35,280 --> 00:19:37,600
She just didn't want to be a mistress.

270
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:40,160
Ms. Zhao said

271
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:43,400
that Mengmeng owed a lot of money.

272
00:19:54,240 --> 00:19:57,920
QINGSONG CEMENT CONNECTS YOU AND ME

273
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:01,480
I just got back from a business trip.

274
00:20:02,320 --> 00:20:03,240
Mr. Liu.

275
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:06,600
What I have at hand
is absolutely reliable.

276
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:09,320
I'll show you when the time is right.

277
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:13,440
But right now, I'm a bit short of funds.

278
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:16,480
If you're willing to help,

279
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:19,280
you can wait
to make loads of money with me.

280
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:20,360
Get back to me.

281
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:29,400
MISSING PERSON

282
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:32,400
MUSE

283
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:34,360
"Disappeared from Weiyang."

284
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:36,960
Doesn't that sound familiar?

285
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:41,440
You're talking about the guy
in the video rental shop?

286
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:46,880
That guy was drunk. It doesn't count.

287
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:49,680
Song Qingsong has plenty of women.

288
00:20:49,760 --> 00:20:52,480
Why would he be so serious
about a massage lady?

289
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:55,320
Besides, Wolfie only killed chickens.

290
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:58,440
Even if Song Qingsong hired Wolfie,
the murder didn't happen.

291
00:20:59,040 --> 00:21:00,560
What if he hired someone else?

292
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:05,000
Both Xu Meng and Lili were beaten
because they touched his briefcase.

293
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:07,880
Why was only Xu Meng threatened?

294
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:10,320
And the briefcase.

295
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:13,720
Song Qingsong didn't even trust his driver

296
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:16,640
and carried it with him
to the massage place.

297
00:21:17,640 --> 00:21:19,920
What was in that briefcase?

298
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:24,680
A business owner usually carries
important documents,

299
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:26,960
checks, and bank drafts.

300
00:21:29,520 --> 00:21:30,440
He.

301
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:34,920
Why does it sound like you're trying
to defend Song Qingsong?

302
00:21:36,080 --> 00:21:37,400
Really?

303
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:38,320
Why?

304
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:45,080
Song Qingsong and Cripple Du take turns
to be the richest man in Weiyang.

305
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:47,520
They pay huge amounts of tax.

306
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:49,520
Even the authorities
have to show them some respect.

307
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:51,040
You know what I mean?

308
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:53,120
What does it have to do with the case?

309
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:56,400
We lack proof to tie them to this case.

310
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:58,960
That's why we can't act rashly
towards Song Qingsong.

311
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:06,600
I see.

312
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:07,880
Good.

313
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:09,400
You're afraid of Song Qingsong.

314
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:12,720
I'm afraid of Song Qingsong?

315
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:14,840
I'm a police officer.
Why would I be afraid?

316
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:17,720
We fight the bad people
and protect the good.

317
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:20,280
We're not sure that Song Qingsong
is a bad guy, right?

318
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:23,760
He put a woman in the hospital.
How is he a good guy?

319
00:22:25,280 --> 00:22:28,000
Song Qingsong is known
to be a sneaky fox in Weiyang.

320
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:31,320
We can't just approach him
with Lili's testimony.

321
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:33,040
We may alert him.

322
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:35,440
We must form a strategy.

323
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:38,440
Like what?

324
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:47,360
Well… the strategy
is to not scare off the target,

325
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:49,600
but also not come away with nothing.

326
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:50,760
So…

327
00:22:55,880 --> 00:22:57,080
So…

328
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:00,160
I need to call someone.

329
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:02,560
Then I'll tell you more
about the strategy.

330
00:23:02,640 --> 00:23:03,560
Don't be impulsive.

331
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:08,360
What are you doing?

332
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:09,640
Didn't you say that we lack proof?

333
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:11,400
I'll look for evidence at Yuanlongli now.

334
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:14,920
Why do you keep going to Yuanlongli?

335
00:23:15,640 --> 00:23:16,640
You have a girlfriend there?

336
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:21,120
WEIYANG QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY

337
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:22,680
Come here.

338
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:29,040
Brother-in-law.

339
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:30,920
Come closer.

340
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:39,280
I paid you to deal with someone.

341
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:41,360
This is how you handled it?

342
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:43,080
I can explain, brother-in-law.

343
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:44,600
Come here.

344
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:51,960
I've told you so many times.
What do you call me in the factory?

345
00:23:52,040 --> 00:23:54,000
Mr. Song. Mr. Song.

346
00:23:54,080 --> 00:23:57,560
I made that woman disappear
as you told me to.

347
00:23:57,640 --> 00:23:59,280
I hired a hitman.

348
00:23:59,360 --> 00:24:01,040
She and her dad. Both gone.
Only 40,000 yuan.

349
00:24:01,120 --> 00:24:03,960
I told you to do it in person,
but you subcontracted it.

350
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:06,160
For kickbacks?

351
00:24:06,240 --> 00:24:08,560
No. Absolutely not. I swear.

352
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:10,160
I dare not steal a penny from you.

353
00:24:12,600 --> 00:24:13,760
Look at me.

354
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:15,120
Okay.

355
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:17,360
Is that woman really dead?

356
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:18,600
Yeah.

357
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:21,640
I looked into that hitman
before I hired him.

358
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:24,880
He's killed several people.
He's professional.

359
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:30,840
You saw it happening?

360
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:34,400
Yeah. I saw it happening.
Buried in the mountains.

361
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:36,000
Buried in the mountains?

362
00:24:38,360 --> 00:24:39,880
Why don't I believe it?

363
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:42,280
Stupid woman.

364
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:44,880
Writing to blackmail me?

365
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:52,240
Go. Dig up the body.

366
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:56,320
If she's really dead, bring me her body.

367
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:57,600
Alright. Got it.

368
00:24:57,680 --> 00:25:01,280
If she is still alive,
you will disappear from Weiyang.

369
00:25:04,560 --> 00:25:06,920
PUBLIC TELEPHONE

370
00:25:08,040 --> 00:25:13,720
WEIYANG QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY

371
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:16,960
PUBLIC TELEPHONE

372
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:22,120
<i>- Hello.</i>
- What's up?

373
00:25:22,760 --> 00:25:23,720
<i>Song Qingsong is back?</i>

374
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:25,080
Right.

375
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:26,400
<i>Did you get the thing?</i>

376
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:27,880
I'm not in the mood for this.

377
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:29,760
<i>I don't care if you're in the mood.</i>

378
00:25:29,840 --> 00:25:30,800
<i>Just tell me if you got it.</i>

379
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:34,160
Will you shut up?
Are you all trying to drive me crazy?

380
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:37,280
<i>Wu Shanlong. We're in the same boat.</i>

381
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:40,240
<i>If you don't get the thing,</i>
<i>the boat could flip anytime.</i>

382
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:43,120
I got it. Exactly the same.

383
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:44,680
It's in the safe in my house now.

384
00:25:44,760 --> 00:25:46,560
It's safe there. Happy now?

385
00:25:53,320 --> 00:25:55,320
Ma'am. Any instructions?

386
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:58,040
<i>My mom is not feeling well today.</i>
<i>She can't cook.</i>

387
00:25:58,120 --> 00:25:59,960
Huh? Is she okay?

388
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:03,280
Should I take her
to the hospital after work?

389
00:26:03,360 --> 00:26:05,720
<i>Waiting for you</i>
<i>is like waiting for pigs to fly.</i>

390
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:07,160
<i>I'm assigned to a business trip.</i>

391
00:26:07,240 --> 00:26:09,080
<i>Pick up Xiaohe from my mom's place.</i>

392
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:11,000
When will you be back?

393
00:26:11,080 --> 00:26:14,320
Should I ask my mom
to keep Xiaohe for a few days?

394
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:15,560
<i>Last time she was there,</i>

395
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:17,520
<i>she chased mice and fell into the pigsty.</i>

396
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:18,680
<i>The countryside is not safe.</i>

397
00:26:18,760 --> 00:26:20,360
<i>And what if there are abductors?</i>

398
00:26:20,440 --> 00:26:23,320
Well, I'll take Xiaohe to our station.

399
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:24,400
That's the safest place.

400
00:26:24,480 --> 00:26:26,920
<i>Don't let her eat ice cream</i>
<i>and drink Coke when I'm away.</i>

401
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:30,480
I wouldn't do that.
I don't even drink Coke myself.

402
00:26:33,280 --> 00:26:34,240
Fine.

403
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:43,360
Countryside. What's wrong with it?

404
00:26:44,760 --> 00:26:45,600
Get me another Coke.

405
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:47,240
Help yourself.

406
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,480
Kiddo.

407
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:05,760
Do you want to go out to work the case?

408
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:09,760
I've worked hard

409
00:27:10,280 --> 00:27:12,800
and made contributions
on the Yuanlongli case.

410
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:16,440
I can tell Zhao Jie to hand this case
over to you tomorrow.

411
00:27:16,520 --> 00:27:17,880
What do you think?

412
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:22,720
Tell me.

413
00:27:22,800 --> 00:27:26,840
How can they put someone
so talented as you on the bench?

414
00:27:26,920 --> 00:27:27,880
Right?

415
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:30,600
Your dad is experienced.

416
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:32,120
Plus your Uncle Ran.

417
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:34,360
The three of us will join forces

418
00:27:34,440 --> 00:27:36,520
and crack this case in no time.

419
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:41,960
Dad. Let me emphasize it again.

420
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:45,160
Stay out of the Yuanlongli case.

421
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:47,040
And stop going to Yuanlongli.

422
00:27:47,120 --> 00:27:48,440
Never again.

423
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:51,560
Why are you so worked up?

424
00:27:53,040 --> 00:27:53,880
Who is it?

425
00:28:03,280 --> 00:28:04,120
Ran.

426
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:07,800
Sir. How's the injury?

427
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:11,160
It's minor. Don't worry. Come in.

428
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:13,520
Kiddo. Look who's here.

429
00:28:16,840 --> 00:28:18,760
This kid is so rude.

430
00:28:18,840 --> 00:28:22,400
Your Uncle Ran is here.
Also, aren't you going to eat?

431
00:28:25,360 --> 00:28:26,640
Acting up again?

432
00:28:27,240 --> 00:28:29,760
Maybe work is stressful these days.

433
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:34,400
Oh, right. Where were you?

434
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:37,000
Why did you vanish when the police came?

435
00:28:39,080 --> 00:28:42,920
I'm just a teacher.
I shouldn't cause them trouble.

436
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:44,800
Why would you say that?

437
00:28:44,880 --> 00:28:47,720
By order of seniority,
you're their senior.

438
00:28:50,160 --> 00:28:53,200
Come on. Let's talk in my room.
Come to my room.

439
00:29:38,600 --> 00:29:40,160
- Sir.
- Yes?

440
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:43,840
All these things are about Yuanlongli?

441
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:45,480
Yeah.

442
00:29:46,120 --> 00:29:47,960
These are my treasures.

443
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:49,920
And yours.

444
00:29:56,840 --> 00:30:00,720
NOTEBOOK

445
00:30:02,120 --> 00:30:02,960
How…

446
00:30:03,040 --> 00:30:07,200
You walked away without a care
and left them there.

447
00:30:07,280 --> 00:30:09,680
They naturally became mine.

448
00:30:11,240 --> 00:30:12,720
Actually,

449
00:30:13,560 --> 00:30:15,120
I've always had a feeling.

450
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:19,320
I've always felt that the missing people
in Yuanlongli in the past few years…

451
00:30:19,400 --> 00:30:20,080
SONG QINGSONG

452
00:30:20,160 --> 00:30:23,880
…were related to Xu Meng
and her father's case 18 years ago.

453
00:30:23,960 --> 00:30:26,240
You saw it today.

454
00:30:26,320 --> 00:30:29,080
A kid hid in Yuanlongli

455
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:31,400
and attacked whoever he saw.

456
00:30:31,480 --> 00:30:33,680
Isn't it weird?

457
00:30:33,760 --> 00:30:36,440
Shouldn't we look into Yuanlongli?

458
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:45,000
Sir, we found the kid.

459
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:47,240
Just leave it to the police.

460
00:30:47,760 --> 00:30:49,600
We're not qualified to intervene.

461
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:54,600
Yeah. We're not qualified.

462
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:57,760
You left. I retired.

463
00:30:58,760 --> 00:31:01,960
But this is Xiaohe's first case,
after all.

464
00:31:02,720 --> 00:31:04,080
Xiaohe's case?

465
00:31:04,160 --> 00:31:05,400
Yeah.

466
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:07,840
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

467
00:31:08,520 --> 00:31:10,680
Zhao Jie just announced it this evening.

468
00:31:16,400 --> 00:31:19,840
Xiaohe is still young.
This is her first case.

469
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:22,560
She doesn't catch on
as fast as you did back then.

470
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:24,640
This kid is way too stubborn.

471
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:28,440
She clearly needs help,
but just doesn't say it.

472
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:30,280
Ran.

473
00:31:30,360 --> 00:31:32,480
I genuinely hope

474
00:31:32,560 --> 00:31:35,200
that the two of us can join hands again

475
00:31:35,280 --> 00:31:37,080
to help Xiaohe.

476
00:31:38,280 --> 00:31:40,400
Rest assured. I promise

477
00:31:40,480 --> 00:31:45,040
I will do my best
to avoid delaying your return.

478
00:31:45,640 --> 00:31:46,560
Okay?

479
00:31:51,120 --> 00:31:52,800
Then it's settled.

480
00:31:52,880 --> 00:31:55,080
Let me thank you on behalf of Xiaohe.

481
00:31:59,560 --> 00:32:04,160
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

482
00:32:19,800 --> 00:32:21,080
Officer Ran.

483
00:32:21,800 --> 00:32:22,760
Why are you here?

484
00:32:24,840 --> 00:32:25,680
These are for you.

485
00:32:26,560 --> 00:32:28,640
Why did you buy new ones? No need.

486
00:32:28,720 --> 00:32:30,680
It's the least I could do.
I have to thank you.

487
00:32:30,760 --> 00:32:31,760
Here.

488
00:32:33,480 --> 00:32:35,800
Still, you didn't have
to come all the way here.

489
00:32:36,600 --> 00:32:38,160
Come in and have some water.

490
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:41,480
No need. I have things to do.

491
00:32:46,760 --> 00:32:49,400
Still that thing upstairs?

492
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:52,040
People have been terrified.

493
00:32:52,640 --> 00:32:53,880
You haven't found her?

494
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:56,640
Officer Ran.

495
00:32:57,240 --> 00:32:58,680
Wang Xinglong said you came
to the fourth floor.

496
00:32:59,280 --> 00:33:00,680
Wait for me. Be right there.

497
00:33:00,760 --> 00:33:01,760
Okay.

498
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:10,600
Right. How's the injury?

499
00:33:12,280 --> 00:33:13,760
It's basically healed.

500
00:33:13,840 --> 00:33:15,000
It won't leave a scar.

501
00:33:23,880 --> 00:33:26,240
Go ahead. Business first.

502
00:33:26,320 --> 00:33:28,480
Tell me if you need help.

503
00:33:29,280 --> 00:33:30,360
Thanks.

504
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:37,520
Then…

505
00:33:50,120 --> 00:33:52,200
CASUAL SNEAKERS

506
00:34:03,440 --> 00:34:04,320
Officer Ran.

507
00:34:05,120 --> 00:34:10,639
Do you know the deal
with that woman in 415?

508
00:34:10,719 --> 00:34:13,120
- What about her?
- She was being kept as a mistress.

509
00:34:14,159 --> 00:34:15,040
True.

510
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:17,880
The one who kept her was an old man.

511
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:19,239
In his seventies.

512
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:24,520
Last winter, the old man slipped
on the stairs and fell.

513
00:34:24,600 --> 00:34:26,639
Cerebral hemorrhage. He died.

514
00:34:26,719 --> 00:34:29,880
That apartment she lives in
belonged to that old man.

515
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:35,120
But it seems that he never gave it
to that woman.

516
00:34:35,199 --> 00:34:38,960
Why did she do that? She's so pretty.

517
00:34:39,040 --> 00:34:42,560
She could have married any decent guy.

518
00:34:42,639 --> 00:34:44,679
Why did she pick an old man?

519
00:34:54,560 --> 00:34:56,520
Officer Ran. We're here.

520
00:34:58,920 --> 00:35:01,200
After Pattia was seized,

521
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:05,240
Mr. Song gave us the keys
to these two floors

522
00:35:05,320 --> 00:35:07,160
and asked us to look for tenants.

523
00:35:07,240 --> 00:35:08,680
This half belongs to merchants.

524
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:12,520
The left-hand side
used to be Pattia's dorm.

525
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:13,920
Which one should we check first?

526
00:35:15,480 --> 00:35:19,000
QIHUANG CLINIC

527
00:35:33,720 --> 00:35:35,880
<i>Raid! Raid!</i>

528
00:35:38,960 --> 00:35:40,560
PRIVATE ROOM 3

529
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:44,440
That one.

530
00:35:44,520 --> 00:35:45,360
Okay.

531
00:36:09,320 --> 00:36:11,080
ANSWER

532
00:36:15,280 --> 00:36:16,880
I DON'T BELIEVE DREAMS ARE FALSE
I DON'T BELIEVE DEATH HAS NO RETRIBUTION

533
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:17,960
IF THE SEA IS DESTINED TO BURST ITS DIKES

534
00:36:18,040 --> 00:36:19,360
LET ALL THE BITTER WATERS
POUR INTO MY HEART

535
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:27,480
MENGMENG NO.23

536
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:31,600
It's their work badge in Pattia.

537
00:36:38,960 --> 00:36:40,680
This is Mengmeng. Do you know her?

538
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:42,840
The missing ghost?

539
00:36:43,560 --> 00:36:45,440
A suspected missing person.

540
00:36:48,280 --> 00:36:49,600
I can't tell.

541
00:36:49,680 --> 00:36:53,160
There are 20 or 30 young ladies
coming and going here,

542
00:36:53,240 --> 00:36:54,880
all heavily made up.

543
00:36:54,960 --> 00:36:57,800
I don't recognize her without makeup.

544
00:37:01,560 --> 00:37:03,320
It's also a dorm next door.

545
00:37:03,400 --> 00:37:05,840
Someone is still living here?

546
00:37:08,080 --> 00:37:09,280
Worker of Pattia.

547
00:37:14,760 --> 00:37:16,640
In the front. Where is she?

548
00:37:17,240 --> 00:37:18,400
Where did she go?

549
00:37:35,960 --> 00:37:37,600
Don't throw my cards away.

550
00:37:37,680 --> 00:37:40,200
Where is the gaming machine? Take it out.

551
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:42,320
Do you hear me? I'm counting to three.

552
00:37:42,400 --> 00:37:44,360
One. Two.

553
00:37:45,280 --> 00:37:46,280
Hey!

554
00:37:48,160 --> 00:37:49,440
How come it's you?

555
00:37:49,520 --> 00:37:51,240
You scared me to death.

556
00:37:56,720 --> 00:37:59,080
This kid plays games all day.

557
00:37:59,160 --> 00:38:00,560
He's ruined.

558
00:38:04,040 --> 00:38:05,960
- Thanks.
- I forbid him to play.

559
00:38:06,880 --> 00:38:11,040
Well, he hid in the corridor
and kept playing.

560
00:38:12,080 --> 00:38:13,360
What are you wearing?

561
00:38:13,440 --> 00:38:14,360
Women's clothes?

562
00:38:14,440 --> 00:38:15,960
You think I'll go easy on you?

563
00:38:17,920 --> 00:38:20,280
Ma'am, calm down.

564
00:38:20,360 --> 00:38:21,520
He's just a kid.

565
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:27,680
- Unbelievable.
- Ma'am.

566
00:38:28,480 --> 00:38:29,840
These…

567
00:38:32,600 --> 00:38:34,400
Playing games all day long.

568
00:38:35,520 --> 00:38:37,640
It's summer vacation. So I'm playing.

569
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:38,960
- What's the big deal?
- "What's the big deal"?

570
00:38:40,040 --> 00:38:43,400
Ma'am, I'm here to learn
about the missing person.

571
00:38:43,480 --> 00:38:46,520
They say this floor
was Pattia's staff dorm before.

572
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:50,320
Pattia was seized before I moved here.

573
00:38:50,400 --> 00:38:54,240
Have you seen anything weird
in the building recently?

574
00:38:55,560 --> 00:38:58,080
The two next door moved out last month.

575
00:38:58,160 --> 00:38:59,480
Business was bad.

576
00:39:00,240 --> 00:39:03,120
The one across, 1703, is a residence.

577
00:39:03,200 --> 00:39:05,880
We only hear men and women
crying and shouting

578
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:07,520
in the middle of the night.

579
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:09,320
It's so…

580
00:39:11,040 --> 00:39:12,120
You know?

581
00:39:13,480 --> 00:39:15,880
So, 1703 is not a store?

582
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:18,600
Officer Ran. I forgot.

583
00:39:18,680 --> 00:39:21,400
Room 1703 is the biggest.

584
00:39:21,480 --> 00:39:22,800
Mr. Song keeps it for himself.

585
00:39:24,720 --> 00:39:29,280
They say Mr. Song
keeps his mistress in 1703.

586
00:39:29,360 --> 00:39:30,320
Shush!

587
00:39:33,240 --> 00:39:35,920
Ma'am, have you seen him

588
00:39:36,960 --> 00:39:38,160
bringing anyone?

589
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:42,800
But often, some flashy-dressed women

590
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:44,680
come to get clothes altered.

591
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:46,840
Guess what.

592
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:50,280
The thing is, it's never
the same person twice.

593
00:39:53,520 --> 00:39:56,080
Ma'am, have you seen this woman?

594
00:39:57,400 --> 00:39:58,600
How can I remember?

595
00:39:58,680 --> 00:40:00,920
I do my best to avoid them. What bad luck.

596
00:40:02,960 --> 00:40:06,560
Don't you want to ask about 1703?

597
00:40:06,640 --> 00:40:07,680
Mr. Song is home.

598
00:40:09,200 --> 00:40:10,680
Song Qingsong is home?

599
00:40:10,760 --> 00:40:12,040
Yeah.

600
00:40:12,560 --> 00:40:15,840
That door squeaks whenever it opens.

601
00:40:15,920 --> 00:40:18,080
I would know if he comes out.

602
00:40:45,440 --> 00:40:47,560
What is this?

603
00:40:51,560 --> 00:40:52,480
Mr. Song.

604
00:40:53,520 --> 00:40:56,200
Are you home? I'm the property manager.

605
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:01,040
Mr. Song.

606
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:03,560
Mr. Song.

607
00:41:09,320 --> 00:41:10,160
Hello.

608
00:41:10,240 --> 00:41:11,880
Police, Nanshan Branch.

609
00:41:11,960 --> 00:41:13,560
I have some questions.

610
00:41:13,640 --> 00:41:15,560
I know you're home. Please open the door.

611
00:41:19,920 --> 00:41:20,960
Mr. Song.

612
00:41:25,360 --> 00:41:26,520
Are you Song Qingsong?

613
00:41:27,200 --> 00:41:30,360
No. I'm Mr. Song's secretary.

614
00:41:30,440 --> 00:41:31,720
I came to get some papers.

615
00:41:31,800 --> 00:41:33,240
What can I do for you?

616
00:41:36,120 --> 00:41:38,520
- Let me take a look.
- I'm afraid I can't.

617
00:41:39,960 --> 00:41:41,560
This is not my place.

618
00:41:41,640 --> 00:41:43,520
I don't have a say here.

619
00:41:44,520 --> 00:41:45,840
When is he coming back?

620
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:48,960
Well… I'm not sure.

621
00:41:49,040 --> 00:41:52,360
He usually gets drunk at night
and sleeps here.

622
00:41:57,120 --> 00:41:59,600
Officer, he's in a hurry for these files.

623
00:41:59,680 --> 00:42:01,880
If you've got nothing else,
please head back.

624
00:42:04,240 --> 00:42:05,840
It's too hot. Can I have some water?

625
00:42:05,920 --> 00:42:06,800
The water is out.

626
00:42:07,720 --> 00:42:10,560
- Coke is fine, too.
- Coke is for me.

627
00:42:20,120 --> 00:42:21,120
Shit!

628
00:42:21,200 --> 00:42:22,760
This guy is a burglar.

629
00:42:22,840 --> 00:42:24,920
Ouch. Ma Qiang. Push.

630
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:26,960
This guy is a burglar.

631
00:42:28,120 --> 00:42:29,560
- Lock the door.
- Okay.

632
00:42:37,960 --> 00:42:38,960
Go.

633
00:42:39,040 --> 00:42:41,960
Dad. What's the next move
of the horse stance side strike?

634
00:42:42,040 --> 00:42:44,080
Kick. Throat lock.

635
00:42:46,880 --> 00:42:48,440
Teach me again.

636
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:52,680
You're biting off more than you can chew.

637
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:57,520
GOLDEN ROCK AUDIO SHOP OPENING

638
00:42:57,600 --> 00:42:59,760
The rock singers all look weird.

639
00:43:00,360 --> 00:43:02,120
Rocking and rolling.
How can they look good?

640
00:43:03,200 --> 00:43:05,360
What a heavy bag for a third grader.

641
00:43:06,200 --> 00:43:09,960
The teachers and parents
are oppressing children.

642
00:43:10,040 --> 00:43:12,080
Dad. Are we going to Grandma's?

643
00:43:12,160 --> 00:43:13,480
Do you like Grandma's place, kiddo?

644
00:43:13,560 --> 00:43:14,600
Yeah, of course.

645
00:43:14,680 --> 00:43:16,480
She has Hua and Huang.

646
00:43:16,560 --> 00:43:18,760
We can catch mice in the yard.

647
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:20,280
Then let's go to Grandma's.

648
00:43:22,080 --> 00:43:23,920
- Dad, you're the best.
- Get in.

649
00:43:29,120 --> 00:43:31,920
<i>Got a lead. Return to the unit. Ran.</i>

650
00:43:38,080 --> 00:43:41,560
Xiaohe. We won't go to Grandma's yet.

651
00:43:42,160 --> 00:43:44,400
Dad. You're going back on your word again.

652
00:43:45,600 --> 00:43:48,640
Want to see where Dad works?

653
00:43:48,720 --> 00:43:49,960
The police station?

654
00:43:50,040 --> 00:43:52,240
Are there a lot of bad people
locked up there?

655
00:43:52,320 --> 00:43:53,240
Are you afraid?

656
00:43:53,320 --> 00:43:56,040
Not at all. My dad catches bad guys.

657
00:43:56,840 --> 00:43:57,720
Alright, sit tight.

658
00:44:07,480 --> 00:44:09,680
Slow down. What's the rush?

659
00:44:10,240 --> 00:44:11,640
Officer Zhang. Officer Li.

660
00:44:11,720 --> 00:44:12,640
You clown.

661
00:44:12,720 --> 00:44:14,280
You're kind of a regular here.

662
00:44:14,360 --> 00:44:15,360
Can't bear to leave, huh?

663
00:44:16,320 --> 00:44:18,720
- Thanks. You helped us a lot.
- No problem.

664
00:44:22,280 --> 00:44:24,960
I'd like to borrow the loot.

665
00:44:25,880 --> 00:44:26,760
Huh?

666
00:44:30,560 --> 00:44:33,000
Dad. What did he do?

667
00:44:34,240 --> 00:44:36,400
Officer He. Long time no see.

668
00:44:36,480 --> 00:44:38,000
Keep your mouth shut.

669
00:44:38,080 --> 00:44:39,440
Just saying hi.

670
00:44:39,520 --> 00:44:40,800
He's a pickpocket.

671
00:44:40,880 --> 00:44:42,360
I've caught him before.

672
00:44:43,040 --> 00:44:44,560
Does he really pick pockets?

673
00:44:46,440 --> 00:44:48,800
Xiaohe. Say hi to Uncle Ran.

674
00:44:48,880 --> 00:44:49,840
Hello, Xiaohe.

675
00:44:51,720 --> 00:44:55,080
You're Uncle Ran, the graduate from PPSUC?

676
00:44:56,120 --> 00:44:57,640
You're pretty well-informed.

677
00:44:57,720 --> 00:45:01,560
My mom told my dad to learn from you.

678
00:45:01,640 --> 00:45:03,240
Don't talk nonsense.

679
00:45:03,320 --> 00:45:04,680
How am I talking nonsense?

680
00:45:04,760 --> 00:45:07,480
My mom also said
that you should butter up Uncle Ran

681
00:45:07,560 --> 00:45:09,560
so he can promote you
once he becomes an official.

682
00:45:09,640 --> 00:45:11,320
Finished your summer break homework?

683
00:45:14,800 --> 00:45:17,360
Xiaohe. Uncle Ran and I
have things to talk about.

684
00:45:17,440 --> 00:45:18,800
Go to the office. Finish your homework.

685
00:45:18,880 --> 00:45:21,040
No. I’m going to play
basketball in the yard.

686
00:45:21,120 --> 00:45:22,280
Hey you!

687
00:45:22,360 --> 00:45:25,320
Uncle Ran. Come play when you're done.

688
00:45:25,400 --> 00:45:26,520
What a kid…

689
00:45:29,240 --> 00:45:30,960
Right, He. Song Qingsong…

690
00:45:31,040 --> 00:45:33,240
I've figured out what to do about him.

691
00:45:33,320 --> 00:45:34,760
Let's wait for him outside
the cement factory.

692
00:45:34,840 --> 00:45:36,120
- Once he comes out…
- No.

693
00:45:36,200 --> 00:45:37,920
He will be here soon.

694
00:45:39,080 --> 00:45:40,000
Huh?
